weather.text: ay : Cloudy, with a high of 67. Winds NE at 10-15 mph.  Friday : Cloudy, with an afternoon high of 67. Winds ENE at 10-15 mph, with gusts to 25 mph.  Saturday : Cloudy, with a high of 62. Winds NNE at 10-15 mph.  Sunday : Cloudy, breezy and cooler, with showers and a high of 59. Winds ENE at 15-20 mph, gusting to 30 mph. Due to the threat of inclement weather, final-round tee times took place between 6:45-8:46 a.m. in threesomes off Nos. 1 and 10.

notes:
An alternate in the field when the week began, PGA TOUR rookie Derek Ernst defeated David Lynn with a par-4 on the first playoff hole(No. 18)to win the 2013 Wells Fargo Championship. The two finished at 8-under-par 280, the highest winning total in tournament history. The previous high was by David Toms (278)in 2003.   
   
 With his victory, Derek Ernst became the second rookie and the youngest player(22 years, 11 months, 19 days)to win on the PGA TOUR in 2013, ahead of Russell Henley (Sony Open in Hawaii, 23 years, 9 months 1 day).   
   
 The 2013 playoff between Derek Ernst and David Lynn was the sixth playoff in tournament history and third consecutive(2004-06, 2011-13).   
   
   Derek Ernst moved from No. 196 to No. 32 in the FedExCup standings(528 points)with his victory at the 2013 Wells Fargo Championship.   
   
   Derek Ernst played The Green Mile(Nos. 16-18)in 2-under for the week.   
   
 Below are the youngest winners in Wells Fargo Championship history:  
  
2010.....Rory McIlroy.........20 years, 11 months, 28 days  
  
2008.....Anthony Kim........22 years, 10 months, 15 days  
  
2013.....Derek Ernst.........22 years, 11 months, 19 days  
  
2012.....Rickie Fowler.......23 years, 4 months, 23 days  
  
2009.....Sean O'Hair.........26 years, 9 months, 22 days  
  
   Phil Mickelson holds the Wells Fargo Championship record for the most top-10 finishes. He has seven in 10 appearances, including a solo third in 2013.   
   
   Phil Mickelson made his 15th PGA TOUR start in North Carolina, at the 2013 Wells Fargo Championship, and he remains winless in the state after finishing third in 2013. In addition to 10 starts at Quail Hollow, he played the Wyndham Championship at Forrest Oaks Country Club in Greensboro in 1993(tied for 50th), 1997(tied for ninth)and 1998(tied for sixth). In the U.S. Open at Pinehurst's No. 2, he finished runner-up in 1999 and tied for 33rd in 2005.   
   
   Lucas Glover (2011)is the only player in the history of the Wells Fargo Championship to post all four rounds in the 60s.   
   
 The 54-hole leader has won just three of 11 Wells Fargo Championships. They are David Toms (2003);   Jim Furyk (2006) ; and Anthony Kim (2008).   
   
 The last four winners of the Wells Fargo Championship have missed the cut(36-hole or 54-hole)the following year: Rickie Fowler (2012);   Lucas Glover (2011);   Rory McIlroy (2010)and Sean O'Hair (2009).   
   
   Ryan Moore became the fourth player in Wells Fargo Championship history to hit all 18 greens(first round). The other three are Hunter Mahan and Heath Slocum in 2012 and Chris Smith in 2003.
